11/05/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian President Boris Tadic launched an initiative Tuesday (10 May) for reaching a political agreement on EU accession. 
Tadic sent copies of a draft document to leaders of the main parties and relevant institutions in Serbia. 
His office said that revisions are expected and that the final version would be ready in about a month.
In other news Tuesday, Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic said his US counterpart, George W. 
Bush, has expressed readiness to help the federal union's accelerated entry into NATO's Partnership for Peace programme. 
Marovic met with Bush in Moscow earlier this week. 
(Danas, Beta - 11/05/05; Beta - 10/05/05)
